<subSubSection id="7BAA8FF59E779C3883DFF2F6A3A0213B" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E779C3883DFF2F6A29122CB" blockId="5.[192,659,1468,1492]" box="[192,659,1468,1492]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="68476B129E779C3883DFF2F6A29122CB" bold="true" box="[192,659,1468,1492]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3883DFF2F6A29122CB" authority="Thomson, 1860" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[192,659,1468,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Acanthoderini">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3883DFF2F6A29122CB" bold="true" box="[192,659,1468,1492]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">ACANTHODERINI Thomson, 1860</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E779C3883F7F2A6A3A0213B" blockId="5.[192,1440,1516,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="5721A18F9E779C38827CF2A6A29E211B" author="Santos-Silva, A. &amp; J. P. Botero &amp; J. E. Wappes" box="[355,668,1516,1540]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref6386" refString="Santos-Silva, A., J. P. Botero, and J. E. Wappes. 2020. Neotropical Acanthoderini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Synonymies and new status in some genera, new species, transferences and new distributional records. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 60: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2020">Santos-Silva et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
published a work regarding some genera of 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3887D7F2A6A578211B" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[1224,1402,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Acanthoderini">Acanthoderini</taxonomicName>
, in which some mistakes were found; these are corrected below:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BAA8FF59E779C3B83DFF166A5A2262F" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E779C3883DFF166A1B6217A" blockId="5.[192,1440,1516,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
1. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C38827AF166A28E215B" authority="Bates, 1880" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1880" box="[357,652,1580,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plagiosarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C38827AF166A1F4215B" box="[357,502,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Plagiosarus</emphasis>
Bates, 1880
</taxonomicName>
was listed three times as “ 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3880CFF166A473215B" authorityName="Jaekel" authorityYear="1914" box="[976,1137,1580,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Plagiosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3880CFF166A473215B" box="[976,1137,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Plagiosaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”; one in the “key-words”; twice on page 31;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E779C3883DFF127A2D0205A" blockId="5.[192,1440,1516,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
2. 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3883FCF127A292219A" authority="Bates, 1880" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1880" box="[227,656,1645,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Acanthoderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillatus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3883FCF127A203219A" box="[227,513,1645,1669]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Acanthoderes pupillatus</emphasis>
Bates, 1880
</taxonomicName>
was erroneously listed under two new combinations: 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3887E4F127A20B21BA" authority="(Bates, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillatus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3887E4F127A16321BA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Aegomorphus pupillatus</emphasis>
(Bates, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C388158F1C7A41721BA" authority="(Bates, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[583,1045,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Scythropopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillata">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C388158F1C7A36A21BA" box="[583,872,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Scythropopsis pupillata</emphasis>
(Bates, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="5721A18F9E779C3887DFF1C7A13021DA" author="Santos-Silva, A. &amp; J. P. Botero &amp; J. E. Wappes" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref6386" refString="Santos-Silva, A., J. P. Botero, and J. E. Wappes. 2020. Neotropical Acanthoderini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Synonymies and new status in some genera, new species, transferences and new distributional records. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 60: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2020">Santos-Silva et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C388221F1E7A2A821DA" authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[318,682,1709,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Scythropopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C388221F1E7A1E521DA" box="[318,487,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Scythropopsis</emphasis>
Thomson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the eyes finely faceted, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C388633F1E7A1F221FA" authority="Haldeman, 1847" authorityName="Haldeman" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C388633F1E7A11C21FA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Aegomorphus</emphasis>
Haldeman, 1847
</taxonomicName>
has the eyes coarsely faceted. As 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C388092F187A4B421FA" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1880" box="[909,1206,1741,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Acanthoderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillatus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C388092F187A4B421FA" box="[909,1206,1741,1765]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Acanthoderes pupillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the eyes finely faceted, it belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C38816DF1A7A319201A" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[626,795,1773,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Scythropopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C38816DF1A7A319201A" box="[626,795,1773,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Scythropopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To avoid future misinterpretation due to the error in 
<bibRefCitation id="5721A18F9E779C38821CF047A239203A" author="Santos-Silva, A. &amp; J. P. Botero &amp; J. E. Wappes" box="[259,571,1805,1829]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref6386" refString="Santos-Silva, A., J. P. Botero, and J. E. Wappes. 2020. Neotropical Acanthoderini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Synonymies and new status in some genera, new species, transferences and new distributional records. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 60: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2020">Santos-Silva et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, we herein establish that the combination 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C388754F047A56F203A" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1099,1389,1805,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Scythropopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillata">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C388754F047A56F203A" box="[1099,1389,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Scythropopsis pupillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has precedence over 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3882B2F067A2C9205A" box="[429,715,1837,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillata">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3882B2F067A2C9205A" box="[429,715,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Aegomorphus pupillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E779C3883DFF004A13F2099" blockId="5.[192,1440,1516,1926]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
3. Figures 19–22, 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E779C3882BEF004A2CB2079" box="[417,713,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Symperasmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboniger">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E779C3882BEF004A2CB2079" box="[417,713,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Symperasmus alboniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimen was reported to be a male. However, it is a female;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E749C3B83DFF79DA13E2610" blockId="6.[192,1440,215,304]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
4. Figures 77–81, 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E749C3B82BBF79DA2BE27F0" box="[420,700,215,239]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E749C3B82BBF79DA2BE27F0" box="[420,700,215,239]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Aegomorphus ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimen was reported to be a male. However, it is a female;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330FDC7E9E749C3B83DFF652A5A2262F" blockId="6.[192,1440,215,304]" box="[192,1440,280,304]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
5. 
<taxonomicName id="F4B0A7FD9E749C3B83FCF652A305262F" authority="(Thomson, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[227,775,280,304]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contaminatus">
<emphasis id="01C4006C9E749C3B83FCF652A2372630" box="[227,565,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Aegomorphus contaminatus</emphasis>
(Thomson, 1965)
</taxonomicName>
, abstract and pages 18 and 35. The correct year is 1865.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
